<div id="Top10" class="carousel slide" data-ride="carousel" data-interval="2500" data-pause="hover">
    <ol class="carousel-indicators">
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="0" class="active"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="1"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="2"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="3"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="4"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="5"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="6"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="7"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="8"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="9"></li>
        <li data-target="#carouselExampleIndicators" data-slide-to="10"></li>
    </ol>
    <div class="carousel-inner">
        <div class="carousel-item active">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-amur-leopard-copyright-protected-small-1.jpg" alt="First slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Amur Leopard (Panthera pardus orientalis)</h3>
                <p>One of the rarest felines in the world. There are only estimated 70 individuals left.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Western-Gorilla.png" alt="Second slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Gorillas</h3>
                <p>There are only 200-300 Cross River Gorillas and 900 Mountain Gorillas left in the wild.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/Hawksbill_HH.jpg" alt="Third slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Hawskbill Turtle (Eretmochelys imbricata)</h3>
                <p>In the past 100 years, the Hawksbill has lost around 90 percent of its population.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-sumatran-orangutan-small.jpg" alt="Fourth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Sumatran Orangutan (Pongo spp)</h3>
                <p>Around 80 percent of the population has been lost in the last 75 years mainly due to mass deforestation.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-sumatran-elephant-small.jpg" alt="Fifth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Sumatran Elephant (Elephas maximus sumatrensis)</h3>
                <p>Less than 2000 exist in the wild.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-saola-copyright-protected-small.jpg" alt="Sixth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Saola, aka the Asian Unicorn (Pseudoryx nghetinhensis)</h3>
                <p>This elusive animal is one of the rarest large mammals on the planet.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-vaquita-small.jpg" alt="Seventh slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Vaquita (Phocoena sinus)</h3>
                <p>The rarest marine mammal in the world with less than 100 thought to be in existence.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-sumatran-tiger-copyright-protected-small.jpg" alt="Eighth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Tigers</h3>
                <p>Of the nine subspecies of tigers, three are already extinct.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/black-rhino-yoky-e1503486491802.jpg" alt="Ninth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Rhinos</h3>
                <p>There are five species of Rhinocerotidae, three of which are some of the most endangered species in the world.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://onekindplanet.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/az-pangolin-copyright-protected-small.jpg" alt="Tenth slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Pangolin (Pholidota)</h3>
                <p>These small warrior-built mammals are losing the fight against poachers and loss of habitat.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="carousel-item">
            <img class="d-block w-100" src="https://www.despines.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/Hyrax-6891.jpg" alt="Eleventh slide">
            <div class="carousel-caption d-none d-md-block">
                <h3>Hyrax</h3>
                <p>These small, thickset, herbivorous mammals are not endangered, but they are awfully cute!</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <a class="carousel-control-prev" href="#Top10" role="button" data-slide="prev">
        <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Previous</span>
    </a>
    <a class="carousel-control-next" href="#Top10" role="button" data-slide="next">
        <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="sr-only">Next</span>
    </a>
